ECMA-376 Office Open XML — Transitional XML Schemas
===================================================

These files are part of a published international standard. They are third-party
specification artefacts, not part of this project, and they are redistributed
here unmodified under the terms recorded below.

Publisher   ECMA International
Standard    ECMA-376 Part 4, 5th edition (December 2016)
            "Office Open XML File Formats — Transitional Migration Features"
            Equivalent to ISO/IEC 29500-4:2016.
Source      https://www.ecma-international.org/wp-content/uploads/ECMA-376-4_5th_edition_december_2016.zip
            → OfficeOpenXML-XMLSchema-Transitional.zip
Retrieved   2026-07

Terms
-----

ECMA International's text copyright policy grants a perpetual, irrevocable right
to copy and redistribute the standard, on two conditions that this directory is
arranged to satisfy:

  1. The files are redistributed WITHOUT MODIFICATION.
  2. This notice travels with them.

Both are load-bearing rather than courtesies. Do not edit these files. Beyond
the licence, an edited schema would silently change what every test that uses it
means, while still reporting green.

`SHA256SUMS` records the digest of each file as published, and a test asserts
them on every run. Note that the distribution is not uniform — some files ship
with CRLF line terminators and some with LF — so `.gitattributes` disables
end-of-line conversion for this directory. Without it, a checkout configured
with `core.autocrlf` rewrites the CRLF files on commit and the stored bytes stop
being the published ones, while the working tree still looks correct.

If the checksum test fails, do not regenerate the manifest. Find out what
changed the files.

The policy covers copyright. Any patent rights in the underlying formats are a
separate matter, addressed by Microsoft's Open Specification Promise.

Files
-----

Nine files: pml.xsd and the transitive closure of its schemaLocation imports.
The full distribution is 27 files; the remainder describe SpreadsheetML,
WordprocessingML, VML and shared parts this project never emits.

  pml.xsd                        PresentationML — slides, masters, layouts
  dml-main.xsd                   DrawingML — shapes, text, colour, geometry
  dml-chart.xsd                  charts
  dml-chartDrawing.xsd           drawings within charts
  dml-diagram.xsd                SmartArt
  dml-lockedCanvas.xsd           locked canvas
  dml-picture.xsd                pictures
  shared-commonSimpleTypes.xsd   shared simple types
  shared-relationshipReference.xsd  r:id, r:embed and related attributes

Alongside them:

  NOTICE                         this file
  SHA256SUMS                     published digests, asserted by the test suite
  README.md                      what is validated and why

Why they are here
-----------------

The test suite validates generated parts against the specification rather than
against rules restated by hand. See README.md in this directory for what is
covered, what is deliberately exempt, and why this lives under tests/ rather
than src/.
